nss_dp_main: do not fail probe when fixed-link registration fails

swphy cannot emulate PHY speeds above 1000 Mbit/s, so
of_phy_register_fixed_link() fails for fixed-link nodes declaring
2500 Mbit/s ("swphy: unknown speed"). This is the case for the
IPQ5018 GMAC1 uplink to the Airoha AN8855 switch (HSGMII, DSA CPU
port with a 2500 Mbit/s fixed-link, e.g. Xiaomi AX3000T RD03v2).

The failure is harmless in that setup: the MAC/uniphy speed is
forced by SSDK via qcom,port_phyinfo forced-speed, and nss_dp_open()
forces the carrier on when no PHY is attached. Tolerate the failure
instead of aborting probe, and only use the node as phy_node when a
fixed-link PHY was actually registered.

Based on work by csharper2005 (openwrt an8855h branch).

--- a/nss_dp_main.c
+++ b/nss_dp_main.c
@@ -678,17 +678,23 @@ static int32_t nss_dp_of_get_pdata(struct device_node *np,
 	if(!dp_priv->phy_node) {
 		if(of_phy_is_fixed_link(np)) {
 			int ret = of_phy_register_fixed_link(np);
-			if(ret < 0) {
+
+			/*
+			 * swphy cannot emulate link speeds above 1000
+			 * Mbit/s ("swphy: unknown speed"), e.g. for the
+			 * 2500 Mbit/s fixed-link of an Airoha AN8855
+			 * HSGMII CPU port. This is not fatal: the MAC
+			 * speed is forced by SSDK (forced-speed) and
+			 * nss_dp_open() forces the carrier on when no
+			 * PHY is attached.
+			 */
+			if(ret < 0)
 				pr_err("%s: fail to register fixed-link: %d\n", np->name, ret);
-				return -EFAULT;
-			}
+			else
+				dp_priv->phy_node = of_node_get(np);
 		}
-		dp_priv->phy_node = of_node_get(np);
 	}
 
-	if(!dp_priv->phy_node)
-		pr_err("%s: no phy-handle or fixed-link found\n", np->name);
-
 	if (of_property_read_u32(np, "qcom,mactype", &hal_pdata->mactype)) {
 		pr_err("%s: error reading mactype\n", np->name);
 		return -EFAULT;
